ingress controller supports host based and path based routing

host based means the request goes to the pod  ex:/ domain infront host based 
path based means the request goes to the based on the path EX: /app  // after domain



🔹 Core difference (1 line)
LoadBalancer → exposes your service to the outside world (network level)  || Routes traffic → directly to a single service
Ingress Controller → manages HTTP/HTTPS routing inside the cluster (application level)
